## What to write into `memory.md` every time

Add a dated entry that includes:
- **What changed** (features, UI, logic, data model, config, structure)
- **Files touched** (paths)
- **Key decisions** and the “why”
- **New conventions** introduced (naming, patterns, folder usage)
- **Dependencies** added/updated and reason
- **Commands** relevant (build/test/dev/deploy) if changed
- **Backend changes** (collections/fields/indexes/rules/storage paths/events)
- **Known issues / follow-ups** (action items)
- **Assumptions** made due to missing info (clearly labelled)

If nothing changed (e.g., advice-only prompt), still add:
- A short entry stating **no code changes**, plus any **decisions or next steps** agreed.

---

## Safety & hygiene
- Do **not** put secrets, tokens, passwords, private keys, or 2FA info in `memory.md`
- Avoid personal customer data; keep examples anonymised
- If sensitive values appear in code/config, store them in env vars and document the **name** only (e.g., `FIREBASE_API_KEY`)
- Never log PII in analytics events (names, emails, phone numbers, addresses)

